I threw this together for my own uses.  If anyone else benefits from it, that's great.

[color=#ffff00]You will not find new player homes, on the list below.  Homes tend to be personal choices for each player, much like companions. 
Companions mods are only listed as some information indicates they do not exist in the Enderal mod.[/color]

[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/77868/?]Enderal[/url] is a full conversion mod for [url=https://elderscrolls.bethesda.net/en/skyrim?]Skyrim [/url]made by [url=https://sureai.net/]SureAI[/url].
READ all of the supporting documentation that comes with the Enderal Mod
It is not linked here, as it may be updated by [url=https://sureai.net/]SureAI[/url] at any time.
[color=#ff0000]Caution: Most standard mods will not work, and may break your game.[/color]
It is STRONGLY advised against using ENBs that have not been adjusted to Enderal.
[color=#ffff00]Note: I have not used the listed mods, and cannot attest to their playability.[/color]
[url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/1334/?]Mod Organizer[/url] is used to install, resolve conflicts, and uninstall mods. It accepts NMM downloads, and isolates mods to prevent overwriting.
[url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/31499/?]Mod Organizer Beginner’s Guide[/url] /[url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/53790/?] Mod Organizer ( S.T.E.P. ) Video Tutorials[/url]  / [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/53790/?]S.T.E.P. Forums[/url]  (STEP Forums are not hosted by nexus mods)

[b]Save / Crash / Bug fix mods[/b]:[spoiler]
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/64413/?]SafeAutoSave[/url]: Auto saves the game in configurable intervals, and allows exclusions.
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/79548/?]Enderal Bug Fix[/url]: Corrects missing bridge texture
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/77981/?]Enderal Bug Fixes[/url]: Removes “Shout charging”.  It no longer applies. Shouts are now Talents.
Corrects some Talents.  Fixes undead vulnerability to silver, so it now applies damage properly.[/spoiler]
[b]UI / Gameplay mods[/b]:
I've found a few errors in my list I will be fixing for the next version.  Until then, you can also check out
[url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/78118?][b]Enderal - Gameplay Overhaul by Ixion XVII aka Reltilie[/b][/url]
Even if you have been playing Enderal since its release, this mod includes a variety of changes that can make everything feel new again.
[url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/78118?]
[/url]

[spoiler]
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/4862/?]Categorized Favorites Menu[/url]: Replaces the single favorites menu with several categorized
favorites menus, with sub categories.  [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/81837/?]Categorized Favorites Menu Config[/url]: Enderal Patch
[url=https://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/71073?]Enhanced Soultrap[/url]: This is an enhancement utility on the base spell.
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/78162/?]Sorted Item Names[/url]: Revises a few item names for improved sorting.
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/84032/?]Utopium's Utilities[/url]: Utility pack with 22 featured mods, CTD patches, and UI tools.[/spoiler]
[b]Travel Related Mods[/b]:[spoiler]
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/77879/?]Enderal Fast Travel EV[/url]: Base Enderal does not allow Fast Travel; this turns it back on.
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/80556/?]Fast Travel From Indoors[/url]: No longer have to load exteriors to fast travel.
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/81074?]Enderal Teleportation Mod[/url]: As named [/spoiler]
[b]Audio mods:[/b][spoiler]
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/78933/?]Enderal Quieter Adventuring (music options)[/url]: Provide options to reduce or eliminate Exploration or Combat Music
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/77872/?]Enderal Silent Player Combat[/url]: Removes grunts and screams from combat
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/79583/?]Quiet Crows For Enderal[/url]: Silences the frequent crow sound when in the Golden Forest.[/spoiler]
[b]Visual mods[/b]: [b][color=#ff0000]*NSFW*[/color][/b]
Do not use any mods with these labels, as they may conflict with other listed mobs[spoiler]
7Base, ADEC, ALSL, CHSBHC, DIMONZED, UNP, UNPB = These are body mods which will conflict with CBBE

BBP, TBBP, HDT, havok = These are physics mods. Enderal does not recommend physics mods. They can be great for immersion, but they consume a lot of resources, they can be a hassle for newbies, and you don't need them. If installed incorrectly it can take a long time to correct, if you don't know what you are doing.  They also require a specific skeleton for animations (of which there are at *least* three.  And wrong skeleton, = bad visuals.

XPMS, XP32, XPMS Extended = Those skeletons I just mentioned.

They're not bad mods, they just require more effort that I care to explain, because I know CBBE better.  It had more options when I was choosing, before Bodyslide was usable with other mods, and CBBE and Bodyslide are made by the same modder.

I'm don't even know where to [b]*find*[/b] some of these mods anymore.

Also, don't use ENBs, Eyes of Beauty, or Enhanced Character Edit (ECE), as they may conflict with other mods.

If you are an experienced or returning modder, by all means, use what you like best.
But seriously, let me know where to find any of those that aren't listed on Nexus, and I would be very happy.[/spoiler]
